is always a friendly Black man,

305
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,840
or a spicy meatball Italian.

306
00:12:44,919 --> 00:12:48,119
So you're like,
"Oh, the kids come here
for the folksy wisdom."

307
00:12:48,199 --> 00:12:49,479
But Sophie has no wisdom.

308
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:51,480
Just a lot of T-shirts
with puns about wine.

309
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:55,040
Exactly. I think it has
something to do with drugs.

310
00:12:55,119 --> 00:12:57,839
Which I hate.

311
00:12:57,920 --> 00:13:01,959
So, I had one of my reporters
on the school newspaper
investigate Spooner's.

312
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:03,759
Guess which one.

313
00:13:03,839 --> 00:13:05,639
Uh, Dorkus McNoFriends?

314
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:06,999
Well, Dorkus was actually busy.

315
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,639
So I gave Brenda my camera

316
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,599
to photograph
anything suspicious there.

317
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:13,640
And she said she got a picture
of something weird
in the bathroom,

318
00:13:13,719 --> 00:13:14,880
but didn't say what.

319
00:13:14,959 --> 00:13:16,759
Wait. So you think--

320
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:20,240
No, I know Brenda was murdered
to keep that photograph
from getting out.

321
00:13:20,319 --> 00:13:21,839
Holy crap.

322
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:24,640
Sophie just got a new camera,
which I know we can't afford.

323
00:13:24,719 --> 00:13:27,319
Hashtag, get my new camera
out of my bag, Aman.

324
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:28,799
But what if she didn't buy it?

325
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,999
What if she took it from Brenda
after killing her,

326
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,160
to protect the secret
of Spooner's popularity?

327
00:13:33,239 --> 00:13:35,239
If I can find
your camera on Sophie,

328
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,960
I'd solve Brenda's murder
and send Sophie to jail.

329
00:13:38,039 --> 00:13:39,239
It's a win-win.

330
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:42,320
Or maybe we could find
the camera together?

331
00:13:42,399 --> 00:13:43,879
Together? Oh.

332
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:45,600
-Hmm.
-Oh, yeah.
Just because it's mine.

333
00:13:45,679 --> 00:13:48,200
But also your hallucinations.
I could maybe help?

334
00:13:48,279 --> 00:13:49,440
Oh, Okay. Phew.

335
00:13:49,519 --> 00:13:51,319
I thought you were, like,
suggesting a date.

336
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,079
A date? You wish.

337
00:13:54,439 --> 00:13:55,719
A date. What?

338
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:08,839
Holy mother of God.

339
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:10,720
Yes, it's true.

340
00:14:10,799 --> 00:14:13,720
Sophie photographs babies
dressed up as vegetables.

341
00:14:13,799 --> 00:14:15,080
It's our dirty little secret.

342
00:14:15,159 --> 00:14:17,079
But that's how
she afforded the new camera.

343
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:19,480
Okay, but if this isn't
Norville's camera,

344
00:14:19,559 --> 00:14:21,040
who killed Brenda?

345
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,320
Oh, no! The camera!

346
00:14:28,639 --> 00:14:31,000
Is someone trying
to solve a mystery?

347
00:14:31,079 --> 00:14:32,719
No. I was just
asking a question.

348
00:14:36,679 --> 00:14:38,040
Heart attack.

349
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,319
Velma, what is this?

350
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:41,239
Did you eat
all the gummy vitamins again?

351
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:44,080
Damn it, Aman. Can't you see
that she's trying to solve
a mystery?

352
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,880
There you go.

353
00:14:47,959 --> 00:14:49,079
Get it all out.

354
00:14:49,159 --> 00:14:51,079
Yep. Okay. Oh, boy.

355
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:52,599
Still more.

356
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:54,040
I'm sorry.

357
00:14:54,119 --> 00:14:55,479
I thought you killed Brenda
because she figured out

358
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:57,360
the secret
to your diner's popularity.

359
00:14:57,439 --> 00:14:58,480
I get that.

360
00:14:58,560 --> 00:14:59,719
But there isn't
any secret to it.

361
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:01,399
Just good food, great tunes.

362
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,240
And I let teens
have sex in the bathroom.

363
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:06,079
And I'm sorry
I didn't believe you
about your hallucinations.

364
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,800
But, Velma, I told you this.

365
00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:10,800
Your mother didn't go missing
because you solved a mystery.

366
00:15:12,239 --> 00:15:13,479
She left us.

367
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:14,999
La, la, la, la, la, la, la.
No, she didn't.

368
00:15:15,079 --> 00:15:16,919
Something bad happened to her,
and it's my fault.

369
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:19,919
Because if Mom just left us,
it means she didn't love us.

370
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:23,719
Which is insane.
Sure, you were
a huge jerk, Dad, but I was...

371
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:26,120
Oh, my eye!

372
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,239
My book!

373
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,359
My idea juice!

374
00:15:37,439 --> 00:15:38,480
Oh, God.

375
00:15:38,559 --> 00:15:40,000
Mom wasn't taken.

376
00:15:40,079 --> 00:15:43,000
She left because she hated us.

377
00:15:43,079 --> 00:15:44,599
Yes.

378
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:46,560
So you can stop feeling guilty
about your mysteries,<i> beti.</i>

379
00:15:46,639 --> 00:15:50,639
And you can start
changing your personality
to fit in and avoid prison.

380
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:51,839
Whoo-hoo!

381
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:54,079
What? Too soon?

382
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:54,960
No.

383
00:15:55,039 --> 00:15:56,279
No, you're right.

384
00:15:56,359 --> 00:15:58,240
It's time to stop
feeling guilty and move on.

385
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:16,279
Wow.
Are you an exchange student

386
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:18,840
from a more
sexually liberated country?

387
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,399
No, it's Velma.

388
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,000
I'm just unburdened
by the belief

389
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:23,640
I caused my mother
to go missing.

390
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,599
Well, now that you're not
a total dog,

391
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:27,919
do you want to hang out
at Spooner's Malt Shop later?

392
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,319
Yes.

393
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,040
Because I'm just a normal,
well-adjusted teen now.

394
00:16:31,119 --> 00:16:32,079
Like all of you.

395
00:16:32,159 --> 00:16:32,999
She is.

396
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,280
My opinion's changed.

397
00:16:34,359 --> 00:16:36,439
Velma,
do you like playing cards?

398
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:38,879
Because I'm calling bullshit.

399
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:40,880
This outfit
is clearly just a ploy

400
00:16:40,959 --> 00:16:42,079
to make us think you're not

401
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:44,720
a brain-removing
serial killer anymore.

402
00:16:44,799 --> 00:16:45,840
Uh, no, it's not.

403
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:55,440
Enough!

404
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:58,840
My fellow populars, yes.

405
00:16:58,919 --> 00:17:00,520
Underneath
this banging new look,

406
00:17:00,599 --> 00:17:03,199
Velma is still the fashionably
challenged loser

407
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:05,799
